  "doc_id": "43625",
  "text": "Experiments performed with albumin which is one of the most abundant UM and the major compound of the stone matrix [CITATION_1] gave some insight into the promotion of AGN by HAP. Several UM have a high affinity to Ca phosphate (CaP) [CITATION_2] which can be used for their isolation [CITATION_3] . To this purpose CaP precipitation was induced in urine and in a solution of albumin in a high physiological concentration (AS, 20 mg/mL) at pH 7.0 by the addition of P to urine and of Ca and P to AS. Afterwards the precipitates were dissolved at pH 5.0 and after adaption of Ca + , Na, and pH to urinary values CaOx crystallization tests were performed. Maximal OD decreases observed in these experiments after the end of Ox titration are compared in Figure 2 with those measured in urine and in AS with and without previous addition of HAP [CITATION_4] .",
